Executive Profile*
Lih-Shyng L. Tsai Ph.D. AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 20 board members in 3 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background*
Dr. Lih-Shyng L. Tsai, also known as Rick, Ph.D., has been Co-Chief Executive Officer at MediaTek Inc. since July 1, 2017. Dr. Tsai serves as the Chief Executive Officer of CHIP STAR Ltd. From August 2011 to January 2014, Dr. Tsai served as the Chief Executive Officer of Chunghwa Telecom Co., Ltd. from January 28, 2014 to December 15, 2016 and served as its Chairman from January 28, 2014 to December 15, 2016. Dr. Tsai served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer ... of TSMC Solid State Lighting Ltd. (SSL) and TSMC Solar Ltd., two then wholly-owned subsidiaries of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited (TSMC) (now Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited. He was active in the semiconductor industry for over 25 years. He served as the President of New Business Development Organization of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. from June 2009 to August 2011. Dr. Tsai served as the President of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. since July 1, 2005. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. from July 1, 2005 to June 2009. Dr. Tsai served as Chief Operating Officer of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. from August 2001 to June 2005 and also served as its Executive Vice President of Worldwide Marketing and Sales from September 2000 to August 2001. He served as Executive Vice President of Operations at Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. He also served as President of Vanguard from 1999 to 2000. He joined Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. Ltd. in 1989 and served as its Deputy Director of Fab 2 Operations. From 1989 to 2011, Dr. Tsai held various positions at TSMC. At TSMC, he served as Vice President, responsible for operation of Fabs 3 and 4; Senior Director of Fab 3, responsible for design, construction, start-up, volume production and fab operation; and finally as Director of Fab 2, Module A, responsible for operation, profit and loss and process development. From 1997 to 1999, Dr. Tsai served as an Executive Vice President of Operations of TSMC, where he was responsible for six fabrication plants, as well as associated testing service and product assurance. He was Montana State Deputy General Director of Institute for Information Industry (III). Dr. Tsai moved through the ranks during his 8 years at Hewlett-Packard in Ft. Collins, Colo., and served as its R&D Project Manager, Manufacturing Engineering Project Manager and as a Member of the technical staff. His responsibilities at Hewlett-Packard included 1um CMOS VLSI process integration, yield improvement, process development and process reliability. He served as the Chairman of CHIP STAR Ltd. He has been an Independent Director of Lam Research Corporation since September 13, 2016. He has been a Director of Motech Industries Co Ltd since January 27, 2014. He served as a Non-Executive Director of NXP Semiconductors NV since July 1, 2014 until June 13, 2017. He served as a Director at Motech Industries, Inc. He served as a Director of Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited from June 2003 to January 27, 2014. He served as a Director of HTC Corporation from June 21, 2013 to January 24, 2014. He served as a Director at TSMC Solid State Lighting and TSMC Solar. He holds a Ph.D. degree in Material Science and Engineering from Cornell University in Ithaca, N.Y., as well as a Bachelor of Science in Physics from National Taiwan University in Taipei, Taiwan. Dr. Tsai holds M.S. in Computer Sciences.Read Full Background









